Class TaskResultEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • org.jppf.client.event.TaskResultEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class TaskResultEvent
extends EventObject
    Event object used to notify interested listeners that a list of task results have been received from the server.

    • Method Detail

      • getTaskList

        @Deprecated
public List<JPPFTask> getTaskList()
        Deprecated. as of v4.0, use TaskResultEvent.getTasks() instead.
        Get the list of tasks whose results have been received from the server. To properly order the results, developers should use Task.getPosition() for each task.
        Returns:
        a list of JPPFTask instances.

      • getTasks

        public List<Task<?>> getTasks()
        Get the list of tasks whose results have been received from the server. To properly order the results, developers should use Task.getPosition() for each task.
        Returns:
        a list of Task instances.

      • getThrowable

        public Throwable getThrowable()
        Get the throwable eventually raised while receiving the results.
        Returns:
        a Throwable instance, or null if no exception or error was raised.
